newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: Westpac cuts small to medium business rates.
newsitem.headline: Westpac cuts small to medium business rates.

text.p: Westpac Banking Corp said it lowered the interest rates on three of its loan packages for small to medium businesses following Friday's cut in Australian official cash rates to 5.5 percent from six percent.
The bank said it will cut its indicator lending rate, the benchmark lending rate for small to medium businesses, to 9.25 percent from 9.75 percent.
It will cut its business equity line of credit rate to 7.75 percent from 7.95 percent and its mortgage-free business finance rate to 11.95 percent from 12.45 percent, Westpac said.
All the cuts are effective July 1.
